    Riverside Guesthouse in Počitelj provides accommodations with a garden, barbecue facilities and a terrace. Among the facilities at this property are a 24-hour front desk and a shared lounge, along with free WiFi throughout the property. Guests can enjoy river views.

    Complete with a shared bathroom equipped with a bath or shower and slippers, guest rooms at the guesthouse have a flat-screen TV and air conditioning, and selected rooms are equipped with a patio. At Riverside Guesthouse each room comes with bed linen and towels.

    Guests at the accommodation will be able to enjoy activities in and around Počitelj, like cycling and fishing.

    Neum is 46.7 km from Riverside Guesthouse, while Mostar is 30.6 km away.

    Couples in particular like the location – they rated it 9.7 for a two-person trip.

    Riverside Guesthouse has been welcoming Booking.com guests since Mar 14, 2017

    Host Info

    Host Review Score 9.6

    The newly built property with private off street parking, opened in summer 2016 and has been designed to provide a clean, safe, quiet and comfortable living environment. Within a 30 minutes radius of the property there are Pocitelj Tower, Kravica Waterfalls, Roman ruins of Mogorjelo. Stolac Necropolis, Old Bridge Mostar, Blagaj river cave and Dervish House, Medjugorje, rafting and horse riding. There are restaurants, a bakery, fruit and vegetable market situated close to the watchtower. The rooms are fully air conditioned, with cable TV, Wi-Fi, refrigerators and tea/coffee making facilities. Outside there is a large, secluded garden with a covered patio area with a table and chairs where guests can relax. A path through an orchard leads to the river where a private deck with sunbeds has been built to allow guests to enjoy the wonderful views across the river and neighboring countryside.

    I like travelling, reading, meeting new people.

    Within a 30 minutes radius of the property there are Pocitelj Tower, Kravica Waterfalls, Roman ruins of Mogorjelo. Stolac Necropolis, Old Bridge Mostar, Blagaj river cave and Dervish House, Medjugorje, rafting and horse riding. There are restaurants, a bakery, fruit and vegetable market situated close to the watchtower.

    Languages spoken: English
